Former Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Chief Michael Aondoakaa (SAN) has called on people of Benue State to support the ambition of Senator George Akume to become the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Aondoakaa is a gubernatorial aspirant on the platform of the APC.   2023 election: Cleric cautions religious leaders on false…     Nkata Ndi Inyom Igbo condemns non-assent to gender equality…     TUC to workers: Participate fully in politics ahead 2023   According to him, the state stands to benefit a lot if one of its sons is the National Chairman of the ruling party as a lot of patronages and developments will come to Benue state. He urged the people of the state to always be united irrespective of political differences. He promised to ensure that the state speaks with one voice if given the mandate to govern the state in 2023.